sql:
SELECT from_unit_id, COUNT(history_id) AS history_count
FROM conversion_history
GROUP BY from_unit_id;

external_knowledge:
- "conversion request" refers to a specific instance where a user requests to convert an energy value from one unit to another;
- "preferred unit" is the unit that the user has set as their preferred choice for energy measurements;
- "custom conversion factor" is a conversion factor that the user has specified, which may differ from the standard conversion factor;
- "standard conversion factor" is the official conversion factor between two units as defined in the system.
